[07:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Just remember: treat the first image you upload as the initial "Front" view All directional commands are relative to that original image Once we have this image we can use it to generate some very interesting videos There are two technologies we can use for video generation:'

[07:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Image-to-Video (I2V) and Start/End Frames (Keyframes). For Start/End Frames we might use two images from different angles and let the model interpolate the frames between them to get a video However, if you have this need'

[07:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I strongly suggest you just use the Image-to-Video method instead I\'ve done a lot of tests on this Once we have rich angles we can describe a scene in great detail For example'

